HEADWORD: Tapayaxin
<hw>Ta`pa*yax"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A Mexican spinous lizard (<spn>Phrynosoma orbiculare</spn>) having
a head somewhat like that of a toad; -- called also <altname>horned
toad</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

